        "inline_data": null,
        "text": "# \ud83d\udfe2 HEARTBEAT_WAKEUP\nYou have been routed ONE isolated task. \n*Task ID*: EPIC-DFP-MOD-logic-api\n*Module*: logic-api\n*Workdir*: /home/ienliven/Projects/sdlc-factory/workspace/EPIC-DFP-MOD-logic-api\n*Phase*: QA_REVIEW\n\n## SYSTEM CONTEXT\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"module_id\": \"logic-api\",\n  \"regression_context\": \"No active regression reported.\",\n  \"structural_context\": \"## > BEGIN_ENVIRONMENT\\n- **Stack**: Docker Compose (React/Vite/Nginx, Python/FastAPI, PostgreSQL)\\n- **Entry_Point**: `http://localhost:8000` (UI) and `http://localhost:8001` (API)\\n- **Interface_Mount_Selector**: `#root`\\n- **INTEGRATION_TEST_CMD**: `cd ui-gateway && CI=true npx playwright test --reporter=list`\\n## > END_ENVIRONMENT\\n\\n## > BEGIN_MODULE: logic-api\\n- **Type**: LEAF\\n- **Description**: Python FastAPI backend for data fetching, calculation, and serving.\\n- **Responsibilities**:\\n  - Serve REST API on port `8001`.\\n  - Fetch historical data (last 730 days) via `yfinance` on first boot for pairs: DFAC/^GSPC, DXIV/URTH, DFAE/EEM.\\n  - Calculate daily premiums: `(DFA_Daily_Return - Benchmark_Daily_Return)` to 4 decimal places.\\n  - Store data in PostgreSQL.\\n  - Implement explicit polling loop (e.g., `tenacity`) to attempt Postgres connection every 2 seconds (up to 10 attempts) before seeding data or binding the port.\\n- **Endpoints**:\\n  - `GET /health`: Returns strict JSON:\\n    ```json\\n    {\\n      \\\"status\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n      \\\"db_connected\\\": \\\"boolean\\\"\\n    }\\n    ```\\n  - `GET /api/heatmap`: Accepts query params `fund_id` (optional string) and `timeframe` (string). Returns strict JSON:\\n    ```json\\n    [\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n        \\\"data\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"x\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n            \\\"y\\\": \\\"number\\\"\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    ]\\n    ```\\n## > END_MODULE: logic-api\",\n  \"semantic_context\": \"### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\\n\\n### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\\n\\n### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\",\n  \"memory_insights\": \"No historic pgvector insights found for tester.\"\n}\n```\n\nThe SDLC Protocol and your Playbook are your core instructions.\nCRITICAL: If successful, your handoff JSON must strictly validate against this schema:\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\n    \"status\",\n    \"phase_completed\",\n    \"module_id\",\n    \"all_tests_passed\"\n  ],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"status\": {\n      \"const\": \"success\"\n    },\n    \"phase_completed\": {\n      \"const\": \"QA_REVIEW\"\n    },\n    \"module_id\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    },\n    \"all_tests_passed\": {\n      \"const\": true\n    },\n    \"failing_tests\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\nIf you learn an architecture-critical lesson, permanently save it for your future self using the native `sdlc_store_memory` tool.\n",
